STEP 1: Create Emulator
• Open Android Studio
• Tools → Device Manager
• Create Device → Select Pixel
• Choose API → Finish

STEP 2: Check Emulator Name
• Open Command Prompt
• Go to emulator folder
• Run: emulator -list-avds
• Note name

STEP 3: Start Emulator with Proxy
• Run: emulator -avd Pixel_9 -http-proxy http://10.0.2.2:8080

STEP 4: Set Proxy in Emulator
• Settings → Network & Internet
• Internet → Select network
• Edit → Advanced Options
• Proxy = Manual
• Host = 10.0.2.2
• Port = 8080
• Save

STEP 4 (Alternative ADB)
• adb devices
• adb shell settings put global http_proxy 10.0.2.2:8080
• Verify: adb shell settings get global http_proxy

STEP 5: Configure Burp Suite
• Open Burp Suite
• Proxy → Options
• Edit Listener → All Interfaces
• Intercept → ON

STEP 6: Test HTTP
• Open browser
• Visit: http://example.com

• Check HTTP History

STEP 7: Export Certificate
• Burp → Proxy → Options
• Export CA Certificate
• Save as .der

STEP 8: Push Certificate
• adb push burpcer.der /sdcard/Download/

STEP 9: Install Certificate (CORRECT PATH)
• Settings
→ Security & Privacy
→ More Security & Privacy
→ Encryption & Credentials
→ Install a Certificate
→ CA Certificate
• Select burpcer.der

STEP 10: Test HTTPS
• Open browser
• Visit: https://example.com

• Check in Burp
