🧪 Experiment 3: IoT Device Security Testing

STEP 1: Deploy IoT Simulation
• Open Command Prompt
• Run: docker run -d -p 8090:3000 --name juiceshop bkimminich/juice-shop
• Open browser → http://localhost:8090

• Verify app is running (OWASP Juice Shop)

STEP 2: Find Host IP
• Open Command Prompt
• Run: ipconfig
• Note IPv4 Address (192.168.x.x)

STEP 3: Start Kali Linux
• Open Kali Linux
• Run: ping 192.168.x.x
• Ensure same network connection

STEP 4: Perform Nmap Scan
• Open terminal
• Run: nmap -sV 192.168.x.x

STEP 5: Analyze Scan Result
• Check open ports
• Identify services
• Note version details
• Example: Port 8090 → HTTP

STEP 6: Access IoT Dashboard
• Open browser in Kali
• Visit: http://192.168.x.x:8090

• Dashboard opens

STEP 7: Test Login (Weak Credentials)
• Click Login
• Try: admin@juice-sh.op / admin123
• Try: admin / admin
• Or register new account

STEP 8: Check Unencrypted Communication
• Open Developer Tools → Network tab
• Perform login
• Observe HTTP requests
• Data visible in plain text
